  "description": "<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/afilini\">Alekos Filini</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/danielabrozzoni\">Daniela Brozzoni</a> visit the podcast to discuss the <a href=\"https://bitcoindevkit.org/\">Bitcoin Development Kit (BDK)</a>. Hang out with them on the <a href=\"https://discord.com/invite/dstn4dQ\">BDK Discord</a>.</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n<p>We cover:</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n<ul>\n <li><p>How BDK started (00:48)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n <li><p>Why is it named BDK and not the Magical Bitcoin Library? (2:10)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>The first users of BDK (3:30)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p><a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoindevkit/rust-hwi\">Rust HWI</a> (4:20)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>Built around descriptors (7:15)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>The ideal use case of BDK (7:30)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>Pain points (9:05)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>Why do devs keep building wallets from scratch? (10:05)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p><a href=\"https://blockstream.com/green/\">Greenwallet</a> (13:03)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>If you have a working wallet, should you switch to BDK? (16:25)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>HWI complaints (see Python) (17:41)</p>\n<p><br /></p>\n</li>\n  <li><p>BDK 1.0 release features (22:31)</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Sync</li>\n  <li>Planning module</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>",
